	   <a name=105123589512354></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105123589512354><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: SOLO TACTICS</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=147821><span id=Sage>Aggrok</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>226 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 24th 10:36 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At your level its a waste to cast the malise line of spells on blue con mobs and also dont use the listless power line of spells either. Slowing is always a good idea, use your slow spell to pull, then cast root then DoT the mob up. Also stay away from your area effect ( AE ) rain spells, the first wave will most likely break root and the mob wont get hit by the 2nd or 3rd waves ( Infectious Cloud I believe is the name ). <br><br>Once you hit 24 and get regen and cannibalize you will need to learn to cannidance. Basically, you sit and wait for your mana bar to increase, stand up at cast cannibalize and sit back down asap. If done right thats the fastest way for you to regen mana. Also always try to get a KEI before you head out if you can, not sure if a level 60 spell will stick on a 21 character. If not try to get breeze or clarity. Offer to trade SoW for them or for KEI I usually donate 20pp.<br><br> Also try and solo in zones with an XP bonus or get a small party together and XP will usually go faster. You do not need a full group to fight blue con mobs at any level. <br><br>Shamans can partner with just about any class early on and make good XP, but Id reccomend a warrior, monk, or mage to fight with in a duo. With a trio add a wizard, rogue, cleric or chanter and you will have a nice little group capable of alot.<br><br>Hope this helps you some just chug thru and try not to die. XP will come and before long you will be able to solo things that will waste other classes.<br><br>59 Ogre Luminary on Luclin server--Chaotic Winds--Venerable Aggrok<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
